```python
#!/usr/bin/python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-

n = int(input())

# 8 + 4*(10+9) + 6 + 9 = 47
# 35% of 5+4+2 = 2+2+2  * %
# 30/2 = 15
# 1 + 1 = 2


if (n <=1):
    print(n)
else:
    n1 = n//5
    n2 = n - n1
    x = (35% ((n-1)//10)*1+15)/2

    if (n1 <= 1):
        print(n+(n1)*x)
    
elif (n2 <= 1):
    print((n2)* x)

else:
    print((n1 + n2)* x)
```

## 100. Check all 8 conditions to see if you can win the game
The game is this. You are given that N/3  of N (0 <= N <= 400) is divisible by 3. But it turns out your starting number, K, is divisible by 6. The rules of the game state that if your number is divisible by 1 your number is false. If your number is divisible 3 and all of its digits are the same your number is false. You can also make a case for K being false by making any of the conditions false. Then you start the game again and move again. Keep making any of your conditions false until any number of conditions are false. The last time any of them remain true, then that is the last time your will move and the game will be over.
